Directed by:

34
00:04:35,483 --> 00:04:37,436
<i>My name is Perica Šafranek.</i>

35
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:41,709
<i>Dad says we're the model
of an honest Zagreb family...</i>

36
00:04:41,916 --> 00:04:44,746
<i>... and that there should be
a book on us.</i>

37
00:04:44,992 --> 00:04:47,140
<i>Therefore I write a diary...</i>

38
00:04:47,390 --> 00:04:49,776
<i>... so all can be read
in a thousand years!</i>

39
00:04:51,266 --> 00:04:52,902
I'll be right back.

40
00:04:53,263 --> 00:04:55,013
- Going over to Znidaršiæ's.
- Again!

41
00:04:55,541 --> 00:04:57,689
No, we'll chat on Abyssinia

42
00:04:57,938 --> 00:04:59,450
story from the papers.

43
00:04:59,656 --> 00:05:01,849
Fine excuse! Been a while
since you were drunk!

44
00:05:02,054 --> 00:05:04,645
No, no, really!

45
00:05:04,891 --> 00:05:07,243
You've no idea how tight
the situation is.

46
00:05:07,448 --> 00:05:09,835
Only Abyssinians won't
give up, my dear.

47
00:05:10,365 --> 00:05:12,115
They're a tough nut to crack!

48
00:05:12,922 --> 00:05:16,672
<i>Mom says our neighbors
are Babbitts, but Dad says...</i>

49
00:05:16,878 --> 00:05:18,514
<i>... it's none
of our business.</i>

50
00:05:19,116 --> 00:05:22,070
<i>Aunt Bajs lives one floor
below us, has a cat...</i>

51
00:05:22,312 --> 00:05:23,982
<i>... and lots of game trophies.</i>

52
00:05:24,230 --> 00:05:27,185
<i>People say she provided
them for her husband.</i>

53
00:05:27,387 --> 00:05:28,977
<i>But I doubt it...</i>

54
00:05:29,185 --> 00:05:32,696
<i>... since Mr. Bajs goes hunting,
while Aunt Bajs has no rifle at all!</i>

55
00:05:33,660 --> 00:05:36,729
<i>Across the courtyard
are Auntie Beta and Mr. Karlek.</i>

56
00:05:36,856 --> 00:05:39,970
<i>He's a chimney sweeper.
So when he passes by,</i>

57
00:05:40,093 --> 00:05:42,888
<i>we hold a button to make
our wish come true.</i>

58
00:05:55,676 --> 00:05:56,994
<i>Miss Marijana also lives...</i>

59
00:05:57,075 --> 00:05:58,472
<i>... in our courtyard.</i>

60
00:05:58,633 --> 00:06:00,747
<i>She presses shirts.</i>

61
00:06:01,030 --> 00:06:03,825
<i>Coming with shirts are clients.</i>

62
00:06:04,027 --> 00:06:07,652
<i>Those without them are relatives.
When a relative comes,</i>

63
00:06:07,943 --> 00:06:11,057
<i>she pulls down the blinds,</i>

64
00:06:11,459 --> 00:06:14,528
<i>because they have
some important talks!</i>

65
00:06:15,734 --> 00:06:18,768
<i>The old Mr. Miško says it
was better in the old days.</i>

66
00:06:19,371 --> 00:06:22,121
<i>Aunt Mina belongs to us,
too. Doesn't live with us...</i>

67
00:06:22,367 --> 00:06:25,674
<i>... but comes almost every day.
Dad says it's not because...</i>

68
00:06:25,923 --> 00:06:28,912
<i>... we're beautiful people,
but because of the dinner!</i>

69
00:06:31,478 --> 00:06:33,705
You've read this book, huh?

70
00:06:33,955 --> 00:06:35,750
Just reading it.

71
00:06:35,993 --> 00:06:38,106
Lend it to me later?

72
00:06:41,107 --> 00:06:42,505
How do you like it?

73
00:06:44,543 --> 00:06:47,259
Don't know...
It's nothing much.

74
00:06:47,660 --> 00:06:50,046
- A bit too big.
- It's the latest fashion...

75
00:06:50,297 --> 00:06:52,490
in all magazines.

76
00:06:52,735 --> 00:06:55,485
Wide brim,
and the front bent down.

77
00:06:55,771 --> 00:06:57,999
You know nothing
about fashion.

78
00:07:10,675 --> 00:07:13,982
Listen... if you won't wear
this one, give it to me.

79
00:07:14,591 --> 00:07:16,466
Fits me perfectly!

80
00:07:23,062 --> 00:07:26,051
Here you are! Ana,
Franjo's here, we can eat!

81
00:07:26,338 --> 00:07:28,566
- How do you like it?
- What?

82
00:07:28,936 --> 00:07:29,845
The hat.

83
00:07:33,690 --> 00:07:35,968
Why did you give
that hat to Mina?

84
00:07:35,968 --> 00:07:37,558
What's wrong with it?

85
00:07:37,686 --> 00:07:40,834
Come now, daddy! It was
out of fashion 2 years ago.

86
00:07:40,963 --> 00:07:43,713
It may be fashionable again.

87
00:07:43,879 --> 00:07:46,027
She asked me, she's poor.

88
00:07:46,157 --> 00:07:46,986
Poor?!

89
00:07:47,835 --> 00:07:50,824
Eats here, keeps money
in the bank! I'm not blind...

90
00:07:50,952 --> 00:07:52,906
Hush, she'll hear you!

91
00:07:52,990 --> 00:07:55,262
- Let's eat.
- Let her hear!

92
00:07:55,707 --> 00:07:57,457
I'll tell her myself, right now!

93
00:08:01,660 --> 00:08:02,694
Good!

94
00:08:14,566 --> 00:08:15,793
Delicious!

95
00:08:15,925 --> 00:08:18,834
What's in this gravy?
It's so good.

96
00:08:19,042 --> 00:08:21,269
Stop gnawing at that bone,
you'll break your teeth.

97
00:08:21,519 --> 00:08:24,110
There's marrow in it,
it's very healthy.

98
00:08:26,074 --> 00:08:29,222
Ana, wrap a slice of beef
for me,

99
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:31,186
for supper.

100
00:08:31,908 --> 00:08:34,419
Franjo, the beef is
excellent today, right?

101
00:08:34,665 --> 00:08:36,778
Don't know!
Where are the papers?

102
00:08:37,022 --> 00:08:38,772
Haven't seen where you
put them.

103
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:41,207
What, papers?
Here they are!

104
00:08:41,298 --> 00:08:43,650
I was reading
the installment of a novel.

105
00:08:43,815 --> 00:08:46,167
Leave the last page, please.

106
00:08:46,492 --> 00:08:49,401
Take everything and read,
I'll go over to Znidaršiæ's!

107
00:08:49,569 --> 00:08:51,046
Wait, daddy, there's desert.

108
00:08:51,167 --> 00:08:52,246
<i>Don't want it!</i>

109
00:08:52,246 --> 00:08:54,518
Is Franjo perhaps mad?

110
00:08:54,643 --> 00:08:57,393
You know him. Got up on the wrong
side of the bed today.

111
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:02,350
SUNDAY

112
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:06,503
Morning, Auntie,
we're going on a picnic!

113
00:09:07,749 --> 00:09:10,056
Stop yelling like an oaf!

114
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:12,739
I'll go over to Znidaršiæ's
while mom gets ready.

115
00:09:12,864 --> 00:09:14,420
'Morning, madame!

116
00:09:14,542 --> 00:09:16,734
- 'Morning! Have fun!
- Thanks!

117
00:09:21,854 --> 00:09:22,922
Good morning!

118
00:09:23,013 --> 00:09:24,205
- How are you?
- Fine, and you?

119
00:09:24,651 --> 00:09:25,446
I'm holding on.

120
00:09:28,127 --> 00:09:30,241
- Why are you yelling?
- We're going on a picnic.

121
00:09:30,325 --> 00:09:31,200
So what?

122
00:09:31,603 --> 00:09:32,512
<i>Dad!</i>

123
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:36,156
- Dad, let's go!
- Right!

124
00:09:37,557 --> 00:09:39,829
Give me a quick one.

125
00:09:41,113 --> 00:09:42,624
It's good for my stomach.

126
00:09:43,311 --> 00:09:46,344
If Baldwin says: "Enough!",
Mussolini goes with his

127
00:09:46,827 --> 00:09:50,020
<i>...tail between his legs!
- A Mussolini drink?</i>

128
00:09:50,143 --> 00:09:51,097
No!

129
00:09:51,342 --> 00:09:52,740
Oh, come on!

130
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:56,134
They're all rascals,
I trust no one!

131
00:09:56,576 --> 00:09:58,644
Excuse me, that's not true.

132
00:09:58,734 --> 00:10:02,086
You're right about Mussolini,
but Baldwin's the man!

133
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:04,164
Franjo, where's your sense?!

134
00:10:04,568 --> 00:10:05,522
I'm coming!

135
00:10:05,966 --> 00:10:08,000
Put it on my tab,
got to hurry!

136
00:10:08,324 --> 00:10:09,119
<i>Franjo!</i>

137
00:10:13,718 --> 00:10:15,354
- Bye-bye!
- Bye, neighbor!

138
00:10:21,829 --> 00:10:24,261
You arranged this stupidly!

139
00:10:24,386 --> 00:10:26,261
Look who's talking!
If we're late...

140
00:10:26,464 --> 00:10:28,976
...it won't be Mina's fault,
but you know whose!

141
00:10:29,181 --> 00:10:31,170
Excuse me?!
You can't blame me!

142
00:10:31,339 --> 00:10:32,657
Who waited for whom?

143
00:10:32,777 --> 00:10:34,175
<i>Perica?!</i>

144
00:10:34,536 --> 00:10:36,728
Don't make a scene!
What will people think?

145
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:38,247
They can kiss my ass!

146
00:10:43,126 --> 00:10:45,080
Shame on you, such words...

147
00:10:45,284 --> 00:10:46,761
O. K., I can also be silent!

148
00:10:47,601 --> 00:10:50,431
My respects...
Perica, say hello to Mrs. Kos.

149
00:10:53,315 --> 00:10:55,906
- What time is it?
- Don't ask me anything!

150
00:10:56,192 --> 00:10:58,310
Note that I'm offended

151
00:10:58,310 --> 00:10:59,661
and won't utter a word!

152
00:11:00,627 --> 00:11:01,502
Wait, Perica...

153
00:11:10,577 --> 00:11:13,724
<i>It's so pretty, it's so pretty,
our green Zagorje</i>

154
00:11:13,853 --> 00:11:16,887
<i>with its black and
smoky choo-choo train...</i>

155
00:11:17,409 --> 00:11:20,443
<i>with its black and
smoky choo-choo train...</i>

156
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:24,198
<i>Take your seat, take it now,
hear the whistle blowing...</i>

157
00:11:24,402 --> 00:11:27,595
<i>hear the whistle blowing...</i>

158
00:11:27,798 --> 00:11:29,434
<i>Take your seat, take it now,</i>

159
00:11:29,596 --> 00:11:31,152
<i>hear the whistle blowing</i>

160
00:11:31,314 --> 00:11:34,348
<i>it will take you
to fair Zagreb-town!</i>

161
00:11:34,831 --> 00:11:37,864
<i>It will take you
to fair Zagreb-town!</i>

162
00:11:38,067 --> 00:11:40,783
Childr en... let's see what
you've brought to eat.

163
00:11:41,703 --> 00:11:44,772
I took nothing, thinking
you'd take too much anyway...

164
00:11:44,940 --> 00:11:46,656
...and it would be pity
to throw away food.

165
00:11:48,256 --> 00:11:50,290
My Lord, what's that?!
A nut loaf!

166
00:11:51,373 --> 00:11:53,362
Let me taste a slice...

167
00:11:57,007 --> 00:11:59,234
You know, it's delicious!

168
00:11:59,844 --> 00:12:01,161
It sure is.

169
00:12:02,001 --> 00:12:04,354
Only... not enough stuffing.

170
00:12:04,598 --> 00:12:06,473
Don't eat if don't I ike it!

171
00:12:06,876 --> 00:12:09,592
No, I said it
was delicious!

172
00:12:09,913 --> 00:12:11,902
- Perica, you'll taste it? No?
- No!

173
00:12:12,909 --> 00:12:15,898
Franjo, admit your wife's
a wonderful cook!

174
00:12:16,266 --> 00:12:18,731
Don't eat the whole cake,
it'll be better after.

175
00:12:18,983 --> 00:12:21,494
- Let me...
- No, no, it's perfect now.

176
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:24,297
Honest to God, it's terrific!

177
00:12:24,617 --> 00:12:25,526
Delicious.

178
00:12:26,894 --> 00:12:28,769
They have nothing here!

179
00:12:29,851 --> 00:12:31,363
Mom, I'm thirsty!

180
00:12:31,929 --> 00:12:33,758
You'll have a drink later.
First we'll go to church.

181
00:12:34,007 --> 00:12:35,677
Perica, come with me.
I'll buy you a soda.

182
00:12:35,965 --> 00:12:38,317
Starting on booze already?

183
00:12:38,722 --> 00:12:40,597
Excuse me! First, I'm not
going to the church.

184
00:12:40,959 --> 00:12:43,471
And one spritzer
is my own business!

185
00:12:43,756 --> 00:12:45,392
Fine! Perica, let's go...

186
00:12:45,554 --> 00:12:48,020
Besides, I'm not
talking to you today!

187
00:12:50,349 --> 00:12:53,543
I admire you, my dear.
How can you stand him?

188
00:12:53,785 --> 00:12:56,172
- It's so hot...
- I'd be offended,

189
00:12:56,463 --> 00:12:58,213
wouldn't even look at him!

190
00:13:13,165 --> 00:13:14,915
Look how nice it is, Mina!

191
00:13:26,790 --> 00:13:28,187
Perica, stop, you'll fall!

192
00:13:29,387 --> 00:13:32,535
- I won't! There's a view.
- We'll look later!

193
00:13:32,743 --> 00:13:33,891
Come down this minute.

194
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:36,489
Give me your hand.

195
00:13:41,774 --> 00:13:43,171
Let's go,
Aunt Mina's waiting.

196
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:06,619
<i>Like two Iittle doves</i>

197
00:14:08,825 --> 00:14:11,211
<i>so happy</i>

198
00:14:11,462 --> 00:14:14,928
<i>we were</i>

199
00:14:16,097 --> 00:14:20,926
<i>From one little mug</i>

200
00:14:21,491 --> 00:14:23,127
<i>we used</i>

201
00:14:24,448 --> 00:14:28,198
<i>to drink there...</i>

202
00:14:42,348 --> 00:14:44,257
Let's go to the
observation tower!

203
00:14:45,225 --> 00:14:47,691
We've for gotten to bring
flowers to St. Ann.

204
00:14:47,942 --> 00:14:50,056
I remembered in the church
and gave a coin instead.

205
00:14:50,260 --> 00:14:52,896
I couldn't give for you,
I ran out of change...

206
00:14:52,977 --> 00:14:55,693
<i>...and a ten would be too much!
- Just a moment, madame!</i>

207
00:14:55,774 --> 00:14:56,489
What?

208
00:14:58,331 --> 00:14:59,967
- Oh, Lord...
- Don't! Why?

209
00:15:01,408 --> 00:15:03,044
It's already done.
Thank you very much.

210
00:15:03,765 --> 00:15:06,640
I know it's impolite
to attack a lady so...

211
00:15:06,882 --> 00:15:09,234
...but I hope you'll excuse...

212
00:15:09,439 --> 00:15:13,144
...my Iittle intrusion.
Permit me, my name is Fulir.

213
00:15:13,435 --> 00:15:15,707
Pleased to meet you. Šafranek.

214
00:15:16,552 --> 00:15:18,585
It'd be an honor to know...

215
00:15:18,829 --> 00:15:21,182
...where to deliver the photo.
I'm sure...

216
00:15:21,426 --> 00:15:23,415
...it's going to be great.
- You think so?

217
00:15:23,664 --> 00:15:25,891
Only we won't pay for it.

218
00:15:26,101 --> 00:15:28,408
There was no deal!

219
00:15:28,619 --> 00:15:32,005
You can't force us to pay,
for get about it!

220
00:15:32,255 --> 00:15:33,288
- Mina...
- Right!

221
00:15:33,493 --> 00:15:35,607
You've got me all wrong!
I'm not...

222
00:15:35,851 --> 00:15:38,316
...a street-photographer,
I don't do it for money...

223
00:15:38,967 --> 00:15:41,035
...but for artistic pleasure.
- Ah, so!

224
00:15:41,764 --> 00:15:44,992
Take no offense, please,
I didn't know.

225
00:15:45,281 --> 00:15:48,667
So many people took
pictures of me...

226
00:15:48,757 --> 00:15:53,542
asking for money in advance.
But I never got the photos!

227
00:15:53,632 --> 00:15:55,063
Right, Ana?

228
00:15:55,789 --> 00:15:57,937
Madame, another shot, please.

229
00:15:58,746 --> 00:16:00,462
Don't... why me?

230
00:16:01,463 --> 00:16:04,338
- Let him, it's free!
- Look here...

231
00:16:04,420 --> 00:16:06,772
No, stay as you are.

232
00:16:08,456 --> 00:16:10,808
Only raise your head a bit.

233
00:16:11,093 --> 00:16:12,524
Fine, stay that way!

234
00:16:13,530 --> 00:16:15,917
Madam, you've got a very
photogenic face. Excuse me...

235
00:16:16,007 --> 00:16:18,155
Look here...

236
00:16:18,445 --> 00:16:19,717
- Where?
- Get lost!

237
00:16:20,203 --> 00:16:22,668
Don't move!
Look up here...

238
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:23,396
Say cheese!

239
00:16:27,355 --> 00:16:29,628
Done! My respects...

240
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:31,059
May I ask you something?

241
00:16:31,271 --> 00:16:33,941
You make only one photo, or
more? I'd like...

242
00:16:34,148 --> 00:16:36,341
...to have one.
Only I'm afraid...

243
00:16:36,585 --> 00:16:40,893
...I was covering
my face with the fan...

244
00:16:41,020 --> 00:16:43,213
This is going to be
an artistic composition.

245
00:16:43,418 --> 00:16:44,929
Your head bent forward...

246
00:16:45,056 --> 00:16:48,965
...sunlight on your hair,
clouds and sky in the back.

247
00:16:49,092 --> 00:16:51,001
You'll be beautiful.

248
00:16:51,130 --> 00:16:53,083
- Pity it's not in color.
- Think so?

249
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:55,873
- You mean it?
- I'm positive!

250
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:01,033
- Your hand, please.
- Steep stairs...

251
00:17:01,319 --> 00:17:03,228
You're such a gentleman.

252
00:17:04,995 --> 00:17:07,825
We should really go now.
I'm sorry...

253
00:17:08,031 --> 00:17:10,259
May I take the Iiberty
of visiting you?

254
00:17:10,868 --> 00:17:12,618
It was a real pleasure.

255
00:17:13,386 --> 00:17:15,374
Perica, thank the gentleman
for the ice-cream.

256
00:17:15,623 --> 00:17:17,373
- Thank you.
- It's nothing!

257
00:17:17,781 --> 00:17:20,372
I feel dizzy!

258
00:17:20,618 --> 00:17:23,129
Good-bye.
Thanks for your company.

259
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:24,523
You're welcome.

260
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:31,236
<i>You are most beautiful</i>

261
00:17:31,846 --> 00:17:34,516
<i>of all the women</i>

262
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,953
<i>only to be yours</i>

263
00:17:39,078 --> 00:17:42,669
<i>that is my dream...</i>

264
00:17:45,311 --> 00:17:49,300
- Their singing is beautiful.
- Beautiful? Nonsense!

265
00:17:49,666 --> 00:17:52,224
This modern music
is just affectation.

266
00:17:52,344 --> 00:17:54,014
You need no voice for that.

267
00:17:54,142 --> 00:17:55,732
To you modern is nonsense.

268
00:17:55,860 --> 00:17:59,166
You know only Let's Drink
and The Battle is On.

269
00:17:59,576 --> 00:18:01,610
Those are old Croatian songs.

270
00:18:01,694 --> 00:18:03,682
And The Battle is On is from
our national opera Zrinski,

271
00:18:03,811 --> 00:18:06,527
...if you really want to know.
- Tastes differ.

272
00:18:11,083 --> 00:18:13,390
<i>Mina, what does
photogenic mean?</i>

273
00:18:13,561 --> 00:18:15,311
- What?
- You know...

274
00:18:15,479 --> 00:18:17,831
Photogenic?
Probably has something...

275
00:18:18,036 --> 00:18:20,593
...to do with photos.
Ask Franjo.

276
00:18:20,873 --> 00:18:22,304
What does he know...

277
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:25,062
Perica, come and eat!

278
00:18:31,981 --> 00:18:33,970
- You know who he reminds me of?
- No.

279
00:18:34,139 --> 00:18:35,536
- Clark Gable.
- Right!

280
00:18:35,737 --> 00:18:37,964
<i>From the movie San Francisco.</i>

281
00:18:38,254 --> 00:18:41,402
- We saw it together!
- He was just as romantic...

282
00:18:41,890 --> 00:18:45,084
Today's men are rude
as peasants!

283
00:18:45,287 --> 00:18:46,638
- Oh, yes...
- Why?

284
00:18:46,845 --> 00:18:49,402
I can be ever so polite.

285
00:18:49,602 --> 00:18:52,511
In the office they tell me
I'm quite a gentleman.

286
00:18:52,639 --> 00:18:55,469
We're talking about a man
we just met.

287
00:18:55,795 --> 00:18:58,148
A Mr. Fulir.

288
00:18:58,392 --> 00:19:00,585
- What... Fulir?
- Yes.

289
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:03,943
Sounds familiar! My boss's
relative is Fulir.

290
00:19:04,066 --> 00:19:04,941
Maybe that's him.

291
00:19:05,065 --> 00:19:06,292
Listen...

292
00:19:06,424 --> 00:19:09,413
Listen, he's tall, elegant,
small mustache...

293
00:19:09,740 --> 00:19:12,456
- And has green eyes.
- What green? Brown!

294
00:19:12,777 --> 00:19:15,129
- Green, I saw them!
- No, brown!

295
00:19:15,414 --> 00:19:17,448
And a bit longer
hair... artistic!

296
00:19:17,692 --> 00:19:19,919
Shame I missed him.

297
00:19:20,049 --> 00:19:21,560
I'd have someone to talk to.

298
00:19:22,446 --> 00:19:23,355
Perica!

299
00:19:26,123 --> 00:19:27,679
Jesus and Mary!
Have you seen that?

300
00:19:33,155 --> 00:19:35,303
The kids are shameless today!

301
00:19:35,632 --> 00:19:37,985
<i>Well, some bush-work...</i>

302
00:19:38,070 --> 00:19:39,979
...wouldn't harm you, either!

303
00:19:40,986 --> 00:19:42,020
You scoundrel!

304
00:19:42,105 --> 00:19:44,333
How can you, swine?!
Such words...

305
00:19:45,062 --> 00:19:47,255
Alright, I'm a swine.
Thanks a lot!

306
00:19:48,938 --> 00:19:50,892
I can't joke any more!
I don't have the manners...

307
00:19:50,976 --> 00:19:53,282
...of those novel fakes!

308
00:19:53,413 --> 00:19:55,367
But you can tell I'm a swine...

309
00:19:55,451 --> 00:19:56,962
...in front of a child!
- No, wait...

310
00:19:57,049 --> 00:19:59,560
Goodbye!
Expect me when you see me!

311
00:19:59,646 --> 00:20:01,203
- Where are you...
- None of your business!

312
00:20:02,204 --> 00:20:04,158
It's all occupied!

313
00:20:04,241 --> 00:20:06,548
It's your fault, Franjo!

314
00:20:06,639 --> 00:20:08,514
You had to get plastered first!

315
00:20:08,597 --> 00:20:11,108
You could have gone ahead,
I need no escort!

316
00:20:11,234 --> 00:20:12,631
Let's go back!

317
00:20:14,910 --> 00:20:17,501
Miss, there's a place
for you here!

318
00:20:17,627 --> 00:20:19,934
- Then I'm going to take it!
- For you, miss...

319
00:20:20,024 --> 00:20:24,934
She's my sister, and she's married!
Franjo! Ana! I've got a seat!

320
00:20:25,059 --> 00:20:26,649
Thank you very much!

321
00:20:27,297 --> 00:20:30,683
- It's full, let's go back.
- They can go to hell!

322
00:20:32,011 --> 00:20:34,318
Mom, there's Mr. Fulir!

323
00:20:37,046 --> 00:20:37,841
Hurry!

324
00:20:41,162 --> 00:20:42,878
- Give me your hand!
- Leave me alone!

325
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:44,551
I'm not drunk!

326
00:20:44,798 --> 00:20:47,150
- Don't tell me I'm drunk!
- Hurry!

327
00:20:50,072 --> 00:20:50,901
Thank you...

328
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:53,618
Over here, madam!

329
00:20:54,148 --> 00:20:56,375
I've only one seat,
unfortunately. Take it.

330
00:20:56,505 --> 00:20:58,619
Thanks, but it's yours.

331
00:20:58,783 --> 00:21:01,816
- Please sit, I'll stand.
- No, no, thank you.

332
00:21:01,899 --> 00:21:04,331
- I can stand, really.
- Wait! I'll sit...

333
00:21:04,496 --> 00:21:07,883
...if you won't.
My legs are hurting.

334
00:21:08,692 --> 00:21:10,169
- Franjo...
- It's so hot...

335
00:21:10,450 --> 00:21:12,484
Now you've lost your seat.
I'm sorry...

336
00:21:12,728 --> 00:21:15,682
- This is my husband...
- My pleasure.

337
00:21:16,044 --> 00:21:18,509
This is the gentleman
we told you about.

338
00:21:20,519 --> 00:21:22,508
You're the one?
Thanks for the seat.

339
00:21:23,356 --> 00:21:26,231
Sure, but I gave it to madam...

340
00:21:27,472 --> 00:21:29,699
Perhaps you know Dr. Brlek?

341
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:31,459
- Who?
- Dragec Brlek.

342
00:21:31,547 --> 00:21:33,263
- I think you're related.
- No.

343
00:21:33,345 --> 00:21:35,095
No? Then it's another Fulir.

344
00:21:35,463 --> 00:21:37,452
Dr. Brlek is my boss.

345
00:21:37,940 --> 00:21:39,213
A pleasure...

346
00:21:41,337 --> 00:21:42,485
- We're moving!
- Yes...

347
00:21:51,845 --> 00:21:55,629
<i>You'll fall in love
in a moment</i>

348
00:21:55,761 --> 00:21:58,750
<i>your blood runs hot in you</i>

349
00:21:59,397 --> 00:22:03,068
<i>and the whole world
is so divine then</i>

350
00:22:03,313 --> 00:22:06,984
<i>your dreams
have all come true...</i>

351
00:22:07,549 --> 00:22:10,185
<i>I'm in love...</i>

352
00:22:15,220 --> 00:22:17,777
<i>I'm in love</i>

353
00:22:18,217 --> 00:22:21,523
<i>'cause love makes
our  lives so fine...</i>

354
00:22:21,973 --> 00:22:24,928
Madame, you've got
a beautiful voice!

355
00:22:25,449 --> 00:22:28,199
Don't... I can't sing at all.

356
00:22:28,446 --> 00:22:30,560
Who told you that? You sing
with such a feeling...

357
00:22:30,803 --> 00:22:32,712
- Please, go on.
- No...

358
00:22:32,961 --> 00:22:34,279
I beg you.

359
00:22:35,718 --> 00:22:36,752
<i>If you insist...</i>

360
00:22:38,915 --> 00:22:40,904
<i>I'm in love</i>

361
00:22:41,752 --> 00:22:45,423
<i>singing with the voice
of my heart</i>

362
00:22:46,626 --> 00:22:48,819
<i>I'm in love</i>

363
00:22:49,064 --> 00:22:52,053
<i>'cause love makes
our lives so fine</i>

364
00:22:54,618 --> 00:22:56,924
<i>I'm in love</i>

365
00:22:57,095 --> 00:23:00,561
<i>'cause that is what
my heart desires</i>

366
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:03,841
<i>thank you, my heart,</i>

367
00:23:04,527 --> 00:23:06,914
<i>you know the feeling
that's divine.</i>

368
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:12,835
MONDAY

369
00:23:12,958 --> 00:23:17,151
<i>This morning Dad didn't go to work.
He said his head was Iike a barrel...</i>

370
00:23:17,273 --> 00:23:21,182
<i>... about to blow!
So Mom had to tie it tightly...</i>

371
00:23:21,269 --> 00:23:22,496
<i>... with a towel.</i>

372
00:23:23,347 --> 00:23:25,858
They were selling slop,

373
00:23:26,264 --> 00:23:30,172
double-crossing swine.
They should be hanged!

374
00:23:34,335 --> 00:23:38,006
I'd give anything for
a chili pepper or a pickle.

375
00:23:42,286 --> 00:23:44,161
<i>I'm in love</i>

376
00:23:44,844 --> 00:23:48,957
<i>singing with the voice
of my heart</i>

377
00:23:50,158 --> 00:23:52,112
<i>I'm in love</i>

378
00:23:52,875 --> 00:23:55,306
<i>'cause love makes
our lives so fine</i>

379
00:23:57,989 --> 00:23:59,978
<i>I'm in love</i>

380
00:24:00,746 --> 00:24:03,497
<i>'cause that is what
my heart desires</i>

381
00:24:04,183 --> 00:24:06,217
<i>thank you, my heart...</i>

382
00:24:06,340 --> 00:24:09,613
- You're rarely cheerful.
- Is it bothering you?

383
00:24:09,737 --> 00:24:12,930
On the contrary, go ahead.
It's more pleasant here.

384
00:24:17,888 --> 00:24:19,683
I've been thinking...

385
00:24:21,524 --> 00:24:23,035
Liked that Fulir guy?

386
00:24:23,562 --> 00:24:24,879
Fulir? Why?

387
00:24:27,518 --> 00:24:30,631
See... I think he'd be
a good match for Mina.

388
00:24:31,194 --> 00:24:32,910
- You're nuts!
- No, no...

389
00:24:32,992 --> 00:24:36,583
It  really is a good idea.
Mina would agree, I'm sure.

390
00:24:36,868 --> 00:24:40,061
- Well?
- You and your absurd ideas!

391
00:24:40,144 --> 00:24:41,371
Why? It's true...

392
00:24:42,302 --> 00:24:44,859
...she's a bit older.
But it's nothing.

393
00:24:44,979 --> 00:24:47,171
We all have weak points.

394
00:24:49,374 --> 00:24:52,488
TUESDAY

395
00:24:54,489 --> 00:24:58,318
Bottles and old iron buying!

396
00:24:59,803 --> 00:25:05,315
Bottles and old iron buying!

397
00:25:05,796 --> 00:25:08,024
Bottles!

398
00:25:11,670 --> 00:25:17,898
Bottles and old iron buying!

399
00:25:19,861 --> 00:25:22,531
- Bottles!
- Here you are...

400
00:25:22,618 --> 00:25:24,846
- Mr. Fulir is coming!
- Who?

401
00:25:25,056 --> 00:25:26,282
Mr. Fulir!

402
00:25:28,292 --> 00:25:30,723
Pardon, madam,
for my impertinence...

403
00:25:31,289 --> 00:25:34,721
- Perhaps it's a bad time?
- No, not at all!

404
00:25:35,404 --> 00:25:39,313
- On the contrary! Come on in.
- This is for you...

405
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:40,874
For me?

406
00:25:41,078 --> 00:25:43,510
Take this...
Thank you, you shouldn't have.

407
00:25:44,275 --> 00:25:46,309
Come into the house.

408
00:25:50,388 --> 00:25:53,183
Bottles... and old iron!

409
00:26:02,056 --> 00:26:04,090
- This way...
- Thank you.

410
00:26:06,731 --> 00:26:09,799
Well, the shots
are very good!

411
00:26:10,087 --> 00:26:12,315
I'm surprised
how photogenic you are.

412
00:26:12,564 --> 00:26:15,553
- You're only flattering me!
- No, I'm serious.

413
00:26:16,161 --> 00:26:19,547
- Would you like some coffee?
- Since you're so kind...

414
00:26:19,637 --> 00:26:21,829
You I can't refuse.

415
00:26:22,234 --> 00:26:25,428
- When will we see the photos?
- Come, behave yourself!

416
00:26:25,510 --> 00:26:27,339
I apologize.

417
00:26:27,468 --> 00:26:30,104
Sit down, I'll bring the coffee.

418
00:26:30,225 --> 00:26:31,213
Thank you.

419
00:26:33,022 --> 00:26:33,897
Right away...

420
00:27:07,265 --> 00:27:09,731
- What was your name, my boy?
- Perica.

421
00:27:09,823 --> 00:27:12,891
I'm sure you're going
to school.

422
00:27:13,019 --> 00:27:15,326
- Which grade?
- I'll start the third now.

423
00:27:15,417 --> 00:27:16,564
Really?

424
00:27:20,411 --> 00:27:23,320
- Daddy's not home?
- No, he's in the office.

425
00:27:25,046 --> 00:27:27,796
Know what? I'll show you
the pictures,

426
00:27:27,923 --> 00:27:29,877
...then you can go out and play.
- Sure!

427
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:31,829
Wait...

428
00:27:36,074 --> 00:27:37,949
Here... this is you.

429
00:27:52,696 --> 00:27:54,571
- You've got a nice boy!
- Really?

430
00:27:56,452 --> 00:27:58,203
Coffee'll be right away.

431
00:28:00,448 --> 00:28:02,801
When is your daddy
coming home?

432
00:28:03,525 --> 00:28:06,718
Sorry to keep you waiting,
I did my best.

433
00:28:07,121 --> 00:28:09,586
- Help yourself.
- Thank you so much.

434
00:28:09,718 --> 00:28:11,832
But first I'd like
to show you the pictures.

435
00:28:11,956 --> 00:28:14,342
Perica, you can go
and play now.

436
00:28:15,752 --> 00:28:16,899
Sorry...

437
00:28:19,587 --> 00:28:21,576
Here you are all together.

438
00:28:22,704 --> 00:28:25,613
Perica... can you draw, huh?

439
00:28:25,741 --> 00:28:27,457
Sure.

440
00:28:27,619 --> 00:28:30,528
Draw me a nice horse,
and I'll g ive you 2 coins.

441
00:28:30,815 --> 00:28:31,769
OK!

442
00:28:36,369 --> 00:28:38,835
You've got a piano!
Must be you play it.

443
00:28:39,126 --> 00:28:41,115
Yes... no!
Perica is taking lessons.

444
00:28:41,324 --> 00:28:44,630
But he's on vacation now.
Play something, Perica.

445
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:47,307
<i>- Don't feel like it!
- Thanks...</i>

446
00:28:47,517 --> 00:28:49,029
...madam, no need.

447
00:28:49,995 --> 00:28:52,950
Unfortunately,
here you moved...

448
00:28:53,191 --> 00:28:56,305
...the picture's not sharp.
But this one's really...

449
00:28:56,548 --> 00:28:59,059
<i>...comme il faut.</i>

450
00:29:00,344 --> 00:29:01,411
Very charming...

451
00:29:02,182 --> 00:29:03,659
<i>It's a real pity...</i>

452
00:29:03,740 --> 00:29:07,615
...that you're not an actress
with such a photogenic face.

453
00:29:07,815 --> 00:29:09,963
- Come on... not true!
- I'm serious!

454
00:29:10,133 --> 00:29:12,769
Look at those features,
the expression...

455
00:29:14,049 --> 00:29:16,196
It's wonderful...

456
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,318
<i>Perica... know what?</i>

457
00:29:24,038 --> 00:29:26,833
Go someplace lighter,
you'll ruin your eyes.

458
00:29:27,035 --> 00:29:29,626
Maybe you're a gifted painter...

459
00:29:30,191 --> 00:29:31,941
With kids you can never tell.

460
00:29:32,069 --> 00:29:33,467
- Where do I go, Mom?
- Don't know...

461
00:29:34,027 --> 00:29:36,095
Try the yard,
a lot of light there.

462
00:29:36,265 --> 00:29:39,492
- It's not nice to...
- It's very nice there!

463
00:29:40,101 --> 00:29:41,248
He says it's nice...

464
00:29:43,217 --> 00:29:45,445
Help yourself to the coffee,
it probably got cold.

465
00:29:59,799 --> 00:30:03,311
Here we're at a spa,
five years ago.

466
00:30:03,595 --> 00:30:05,107
- Incredible!
- Why?

467
00:30:05,513 --> 00:30:08,627
What a figure! You're not
aware how good you look.

468
00:30:09,189 --> 00:30:11,462
Come on, you say that
to every woman...

469
00:30:13,545 --> 00:30:14,896
<i>Don't you know...</i>

470
00:30:15,303 --> 00:30:18,609
<i>- ... how I adore you...
- Excuse me...</i>

471
00:30:18,859 --> 00:30:21,131
<i>- I'm an honest woman!
- Mom!</i>

472
00:30:22,215 --> 00:30:23,567
Here, I did it!

473
00:30:24,852 --> 00:30:26,330
- I drew a horse!
- Fine...

474
00:30:26,611 --> 00:30:29,565
Have some more coffee. My
husband will be here soon.

475
00:30:30,327 --> 00:30:33,713
Then I'll go. I wasn't
thinking of staying too long.

476
00:30:34,003 --> 00:30:36,275
- I drew a horse!
- Nice... fine.

477
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:38,390
- Terrific!
- Two coins, please.

478
00:30:38,598 --> 00:30:40,825
You're so impertinent!

479
00:30:41,075 --> 00:30:42,711
It's not his fault...

480
00:30:43,233 --> 00:30:47,380
Here... two coins for candy
for being such a good boy.

481
00:30:47,708 --> 00:30:49,458
- Thanks!
- You're a real gentleman.

482
00:30:49,706 --> 00:30:50,932
It's nothing, madam.

483
00:30:51,624 --> 00:30:54,532
- Have you thanked him?
- Of course I have!

484
00:30:58,896 --> 00:30:59,850
<i>Madame...</i>

485
00:31:00,854 --> 00:31:02,444
I almost for got!

486
00:31:03,371 --> 00:31:04,961
- Pictures...
- Here you are...

487
00:31:05,089 --> 00:31:06,566
- Thank you.
- I'll be...

488
00:31:07,926 --> 00:31:09,642
...on my way now.
- Already?

489
00:31:10,643 --> 00:31:14,598
We should talk in private.

490
00:31:14,918 --> 00:31:17,793
- When can we meet?
- That is not possible.

491
00:31:18,595 --> 00:31:20,469
I'm sorry...

492
00:31:22,630 --> 00:31:24,664
<i>Think about it. My motto is
fairness and discretion.</i>

493
00:31:26,186 --> 00:31:30,095
Tomorrow afternoon in the
Zrinjevac Park pavilion.

494
00:31:30,222 --> 00:31:32,097
- It's im possible!
- Madame...

495
00:31:32,220 --> 00:31:35,413
- It's out of the question!
- Your final word?

496
00:31:35,536 --> 00:31:37,889
Yes... no!
My husband's coming!

497
00:31:51,199 --> 00:31:52,028
Excuse me...

498
00:31:52,718 --> 00:31:54,434
You look familiar...

499
00:31:54,556 --> 00:31:57,511
That's Mr. Fulir!
I drew a horse...

500
00:31:57,632 --> 00:32:00,064
...and he gave me 2 coins!
- Oh, it's you, Fulir!

501
00:32:01,069 --> 00:32:04,102
- I was just asking about you.
- What brings you here?

502
00:32:04,265 --> 00:32:06,458
My pictures from that picnic.

503
00:32:06,583 --> 00:32:08,855
- How much are they?
- You'll only offend me.

504
00:32:08,940 --> 00:32:11,690
I did it as a friend.

505
00:32:11,857 --> 00:32:13,811
Then at least we'll
have a drink.

506
00:32:14,175 --> 00:32:16,129
Perica, fetch a bottle
from Znidaršiæ's.

507
00:32:16,252 --> 00:32:18,047
Thanks, I can't now.

508
00:32:18,130 --> 00:32:19,959
I'm in a hurry.

509
00:32:20,048 --> 00:32:22,276
Hey, what's one bottle?

510
00:32:23,125 --> 00:32:25,477
<i>You prefer white or red?
Perhaps Plješivica?</i>

511
00:32:25,562 --> 00:32:28,392
<i>- If you insist...
- Perica, Plješivica!</i>

512
00:32:28,479 --> 00:32:31,195
- And mineral water...
- Got it upstairs.

513
00:32:32,715 --> 00:32:33,941
<i>After you! Please...</i>

514
00:32:38,828 --> 00:32:42,658
<i>For one brief moment</i>

515
00:32:43,103 --> 00:32:45,092
<i>of happiness</i>

516
00:32:46,180 --> 00:32:50,612
<i>a thousand days</i>

517
00:32:51,055 --> 00:32:54,282
<i>of sorrowfulness...</i>

518
00:32:57,808 --> 00:32:59,000
Bravo, madame!

519
00:32:59,885 --> 00:33:02,840
Dear Fulir, it's great
two of us have met.

520
00:33:02,922 --> 00:33:03,990
Right!

521
00:33:05,359 --> 00:33:07,473
Cheers!

522
00:33:08,156 --> 00:33:08,793
Madame...

523
00:33:10,993 --> 00:33:13,663
What do you do, if I may ask?

524
00:33:14,310 --> 00:33:15,821
What do I do?

525
00:33:15,988 --> 00:33:18,102
Mostly acquisitions lately.

526
00:33:18,385 --> 00:33:20,738
You can earn a lot that way!

527
00:33:21,462 --> 00:33:23,690
With good co nnections.
A guy who built a house...

528
00:33:23,820 --> 00:33:26,570
...in a posh area with that.
- Šoštariæ!

529
00:33:27,056 --> 00:33:29,931
I think you should stick to art.

530
00:33:30,013 --> 00:33:34,081
- You really understand it.
- You are quite right.

531
00:33:34,208 --> 00:33:35,879
But today's provincialism...

532
00:33:36,086 --> 00:33:39,280
Tell me, who's interested
in art today?

533
00:33:39,403 --> 00:33:42,630
- Yes, it's sad.
- It's quite different abroad.

534
00:33:42,759 --> 00:33:44,987
- Ah, abroad...
- Excuse me...

535
00:33:45,157 --> 00:33:47,190
Are you married?

536
00:33:48,073 --> 00:33:49,790
- No, I'm single.
- Really?

537
00:33:49,871 --> 00:33:50,667
A bachelor.

538
00:33:51,510 --> 00:33:53,941
- Told you!
- Nonsense!

539
00:33:54,067 --> 00:33:56,737
Tell you something.
Best thing for you...

540
00:33:56,864 --> 00:33:59,933
...is to find a good woman,
preferably with money.

541
00:34:01,139 --> 00:34:03,497
<i>- There you have it!
- What do you know...</i>

542
00:34:03,497 --> 00:34:05,008
<i>...what's best?
- Not everybody is so fortunate...</i>

543
00:34:05,135 --> 00:34:08,840
...to find such a charming wife.

544
00:34:09,171 --> 00:34:12,477
She's not so bad.
There are worse!

545
00:34:13,446 --> 00:34:16,435
<i>- He's always like this.
- But I'm different.</i>

546
00:34:16,802 --> 00:34:19,189
I need freedom!

547
00:34:20,279 --> 00:34:23,824
I'd join an expedition
to Amazonia any time!

548
00:34:23,915 --> 00:34:25,949
- Really?
- Or Congo!

549
00:34:26,072 --> 00:34:28,822
- You wouldn't be afraid?
- Never! This stout heart...

550
00:34:28,949 --> 00:34:31,177
...could hunt beasts
bare handed!

551
00:34:31,307 --> 00:34:33,454
You're always talking
rubbish drunk!

552
00:34:34,224 --> 00:34:36,815
Told you thousand times
you don't understand me.

553
00:34:36,901 --> 00:34:39,093
But let's not discuss it now.

554
00:34:39,618 --> 00:34:41,970
Excuse me... gotta go.

555
00:34:52,004 --> 00:34:54,152
You must be mad at me.

556
00:34:54,642 --> 00:34:58,426
A great shame if we don't
make some more pictures.

557
00:34:58,757 --> 00:35:00,950
- It's not convenient...
- Don't refuse!

558
00:35:01,035 --> 00:35:03,069
- I've got to see you in private.
- No, I can't.

559
00:35:03,192 --> 00:35:04,306
My husband...

560
00:35:05,390 --> 00:35:07,743
Stop torturing me!
Well?

561
00:35:09,346 --> 00:35:10,300
Don't know...

562
00:35:15,979 --> 00:35:19,933
<i>For just one glance
of your eyes</i>

563
00:35:21,253 --> 00:35:23,401
<i>I'd give my life...</i>

564
00:35:24,330 --> 00:35:26,761
<i>I'd give my life...</i>

565
00:35:28,046 --> 00:35:32,512
<i>For just one glance
of your eyes</i>

566
